With their own brands, the big distribution chains increase their profit margins and boost customer loyalty. Investigation. Also, the brining process, additives in processed foods and an introduction to the Swedish saffron buns called "lussekatter".

The Beauvaisis

In the Beauvaisis, Anselme Beaudoin shares his passion for cheesemaking at the Gaec de la Chapelle-Saint-Jean. At the Ferme du Chassy, Laurent Cnudde discusses organic market gardening and cereal-growing. Damien Top invites us for an immersive visit to the Conservatoire d'Espaces Naturels des Hauts-de-France and reveals the fascinating Bresles watercress.

Presented by: Guy Martin.

programme.title: Paname
programme.desc:
Rue du Temple
The Rue du Temple, one of the oldest streets in Paris, connects the Hôtel de Ville to the Place de la République. We focus on its upper areas: the Sainte-Avoye district, criss-crossed by small narrow streets where heavy portes-cochères open to reveal private mansions or workshops buzzing with activity.
Presented by: Yvan Hallouin.

programme.title: Roumanie, le charme des Balkans
programme.desc:
On the southern fringes of Eastern Europe, francophone and francophile, Romania remains little known. Yet, in the heart of its sublime landscapes, its people have succeeded in keeping their culture and traditions alive. From architectural heritage to natural parks, Romania is a land of untold surprises to explore.

Directed by: Éric Bacos (France, 2023)

The Perche, land of manor houses and picturesque bocage
With rolling hills, forests and elegant manors, the Perche is one of France's ancient provinces. We stroll through the fortified town of Mortagne, long favoured by the Counts and Countesses of the Perche for relaxation and leisure, visit Montligeon, Nogent-le-Rotrou and La Perrière, discover intricate beadwork and delicious boudin sausage.
Directed by: Marie David (season 7, France, 2020)

programme.desc:

The remains of a train driver have been found on a railway line. All the clues point to him having been knocked unconscious then placed on the rails whilst waiting for a train to pass. Investigating the case, Marianne finds each new detail more disturbing than the last.

programme.title: Marianne
